Zambia to Allow Barrick to Buy Equinox’s Lumwana Copper Mine, Post Reports

-- B y   A n t h o n y   M u k w i t a
-- 
2011-05-24T10:34:43Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-24/zambia-to-allow-barrick-to-buy-equinox-s-lumwana-copper-mine-post-reports.html
Zambia will allow  Barrick Gold Corp. (ABX) 
to acquire the Lumwana copper mine as part of a C$7.3 billion
($7.5 billion) takeover of  Equinox Minerals Ltd. (EQN) , Mines and
Minerals Minister Maxwell Mwale told the Post newspaper.  The country, the biggest African copper producer, will let
market forces prevail, the Lusaka-based newspaper reported.  The Competition and Consumer Protection Commission said May
18 it was studying the proposed purchase of Equinox. Zambia aims
to produce 2 million metric tons of copper a year by 2015.  Barrick is the world’s biggest gold producer.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Anthony Mukwita in Lusaka at 
 amukwita1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 